Package farm

Class Tile

java.lang.Object
farm.Tile
public class Tile extends Object
This class represents a tile in the game.

The variables that represent the life cycle of a plant are held here.

    • Tile

      The rock status of the tile is set here.

      Parameters:
      rock - integer representation of the presence of rock. The tile status is changed adjusted on this variable.

  • Method Details

    • update

      public void update()
      This method updates the Tile's plant data depending on the status of the plant.

      If a plant is present, its harvest time will be decremented. Then if the plant is on its harvest day, the code will check if the minimum requirements for that plant have been reached. It declares the plant as dead if the requirements have not been met. Otherwise, the amount produced by the plant will be set to 1 or a random number in a range if the plant is BountifulHarvestCrop. The plant is also declared dead if its harvest day has passed.

    • addCrop

      public boolean addCrop(Crop seed)
      This method works similarly to a setter for plant

      If the tile has not been plowed, has a rock, or already has a plant, planting will not happen. Otherwise, plant is set to seed and the corresponding plant variables in this class are adjusted.

      Parameters:
      seed - the Crop object to be planted into Tile.
      Returns:
      false if the Tile is not plowed, has a rock, or already has a plant. Otherwise true.

    • changePlowStatus

      public boolean changePlowStatus()
      This method checks if the Tile can be plowed. This means the tile should not be plowed and have no plant or rock. If the check returns true, then plowed is set to true.
      Returns:
      true if tile was plowed, false otherwise.

    • resetTile

      public void resetTile()
      This method resets all variables to its default values. rock is always set to false here.
